50|$|The game {{is divided}} into five social stages: Pioneer, Settler, Citizen, Merchant, and Aristocrat. At {{the start of the}} game, all of a player's {{citizens}} are pioneers. They pay little amounts of taxes, and require only food and a town center. As a player's empire develops, so does his population. They begin upgrading (provided they have sufficient goods), paying more taxes, but also requiring more goods, such as tobacco products, <b>perfume,</b> <b>lamp</b> oil, and much more. It is crucial for a player to develop quickly, as not much profit is attained until reaching the merchant stage.|$|E
